Basically what we put in WHERE (SQL)
Constraints are separated by a space which is equivalent to AND

Find keyword in subject:
subj: KEYWORD

Find keyword in body:
body: KEYWORD

Find keyword in body / subject:
KEYWORD

(can add % to beginning or end of keyword to make it prefix / suffix)

Find emails from this email:
from:EXAMPLE_EMAIL

Find emails sent to this email:
to:EXAMPLE_EMAIL

Find emails cc'd with this email:
cc:EXAMPLE_EMAIL

Find emails bcc'd with this email:
bcc:EXAMPLE_EMAIL

Find emails from this date:
date:EXAMPLE_DATE

Find emails after this date:
date>EXAMPLE_DATE

Find emails before this date:
date<EXAMPLE_DATE

